17 (2) Any nominated area meeting the criteria in paragraph (1) of this subsection may be
18 designated as an enterprise zone. Any redevelopment project used to qualify an area for
19 designation as an enterprise zone under this subsection shall, upon approval of such
20 designation, qualify for an exemption of any sales and use tax levied within the
21 boundaries of such project.
22 (3) Any variation in the sales price of goods and services within any redevelopment
23 project used to qualify an area for designation as an enterprise zone under this subsection
24 attributable to lease arrangements between a retailer and the owner of the project shall be
25 a permitted practice under Parts 1 and 2 of Article 15 of Chapter 1 of Title 10.
26 (4) By resolution or ordinance, the local governing body designating and creating an
27 enterprise zone under this subsection may assess and collect annual enterprise zone
28 infrastructure fees from each retailer operating within the boundaries of the project that
29 is a qualifying business or service enterprise making sales transactions exempted from
30 sales and use tax under paragraph (2) of this subsection in an amount not to exceed, in
31 aggregate, the amount of sales and use tax on transactions of such retailer exempted
32 under paragraph (2) of this subsection, which fees may be pledged by such local
33 governing body, directly or indirectly, as security for revenue bonds issued for
34 development or infrastructure within the enterprise zone.
35 (5) This subsection shall not apply to projects involving or related to casino gambling."
36 SECTION 2.
37 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 36-88-10, relating to time
38 limitations, as follows:
39 "36-88-10.
40 An area designated as an enterprise zone shall remain in existence for ten years from the
41 first day of the calendar year immediately following its designation as an enterprise zone;
42 provided, however, that an area designated as an enterprise zone under subsection (g) of
